    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Cancelling a task has three primary effects:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "It flags the task as canceled.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "It causes any active cancellation handlers on the task to run, once.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "It cancels any child tasks and task groups of the task, including",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "those created in the future. If those tasks have cancellation handlers,",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "they also are triggered.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Task cancellation is cooperative and idempotent.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Cancelling a task does not automatically cause arbitrary functions on the task",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to stop running or throw errors. A function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "may",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " choose to react",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to cancellation by ending its work early, and it is conventional to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "signal that to callers by throwing ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CancellationError",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". However,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a function that doesn’t specifically check for cancellation will",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "run to completion normally, even if the task it is running on is",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "canceled. However, that function might still end early if it calls",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "other code that handles cancellation by throwing and that function doesn’t",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "handle the error.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "It’s safe to cancel a task from any task or thread. It’s safe for",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "multiple tasks or threads to cancel the same task at the same",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "time. Cancelling a task that has already been canceled has no",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "additional effect.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "code": "cancel",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " may need to acquire locks and synchronously run",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "arbitrary cancellation-handler code associated with the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "canceled task. To reduce the risk of deadlock, it is",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "recommended that callers release any locks they might be",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "holding before they call cancel.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If the task has already run past the last point where it could have",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "performed a cancellation check, cancelling it may have no observable effects.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "Task.checkCancellation()",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "See Also",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "withTaskCancellationHandler(operation:onCancel:isolation:)",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "See Also",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
